    {
      "kind": {
        "id": "E0026",
        "name": "list-double-semicolon",
        "expected": "single semicolon between list elements",
        "found": {
          "kind": ";",
          "text": ";"
        },
        "fix": "remove one semicolon - list elements are separated by single semicolons",
        "hint": "List elements must be separated by a single semicolon.\n\nIn OCaml lists, elements are separated by semicolons (;), not commas:\n  ```ocaml\n  (* Correct syntax *)\n  let x = [1; 2; 3]\n  let y = [\"a\"; \"b\"; \"c\"]\n  \n  (* Common mistakes *)\n  let z = [1;; 2]      (* error: double semicolon *)\n  let w = [;;]         (* error: empty element with double semicolon *)\n  let v = [;]          (* error: semicolon without elements *)\n  ```\n\nFix: use a single semicolon (;) between list elements.\nNote: Double semicolons (;;) are used as top-level statement terminators in the REPL, not in lists.\n"
      },
      "span": {
        "start": 442,
        "end": 443
      }
